{
  "text": "R4 It should be underscored that, in many cases, it is possible to transform a nonlinearly parameterised regression into a linear one via over-parameterisation-see the discussion in this respect in [CITATION_1] . Since over-parameterisation increases the dimension of the parameter space the excitation requirements on the signals are, of course, more stringent.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "43780949"
